Description: Fragment of East Greek pottery open vessel with white dipinto.
Curator's comments: The piece could belong to the only other vase with dedication in white known from the site, BM 1888,0601.531.
Bibliographic references: Hogarth 1898/1899 / Excavations at Naukratis, A. Site and Buildings (53 and pl. IV, 1)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (no. 523)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.632)
